======================================================================
PART 8: Sign of Pfaffian sum
======================================================================
  THEORY: Ps(T^c) = (-1)^{(n-1)/2} * Ps(T)
    n=3: Ps(T^c) = -Ps(T)  [sign flips]
    n=5: Ps(T^c) = Ps(T)   [sign preserved]
    n=7: Ps(T^c) = -Ps(T)  [sign flips]

  Verification at n=5:
    Ps(T) = Ps(T^c) for all 1024 n=5 tournaments

  Verification at n=7 (sample):
    Ps(T) = -Ps(T^c) for all 5000 sampled n=7 tournaments

