PART 13: Pf_sum and eigenvalue products
======================================================================
  THEOREM: Ps^2 = product_k (1 + 2*lambda_k)
  where lambda_k are eigenvalues of A (the adjacency matrix).

  bits=0: H=1, Ps=+1, Ps^2=1, det(I+2A)=1, match=True
  bits=1: H=1, Ps=-1, Ps^2=1, det(I+2A)=1, match=True
  bits=7: H=1, Ps=-1, Ps^2=1, det(I+2A)=1, match=True
  bits=31: H=1, Ps=-1, Ps^2=1, det(I+2A)=1, match=True
